photo.title: Daylight savings

description._content: Just a month ago, the city would have been shrouded in darkness by this hour. But now this thing they call daylight savings has pushed blue hour into dinner time. What manner of treachery is this!?! (8 second exposure) See big on black. explored 3/22/2010

photo.title: Pacific Telesis Tower - 1 Montgomery Street, San Francisco

description._content:
1982, Skidmore, Owings & Merrill

aka Telesis Tower, Post-Montgomery Center and 120 Kearny Street


Despite address, tower does not border Montgomery Street. It stands at the northeast corner of Post and Kearny Streets, with the Crocker Galleria extending toward Montgomery Street.

photo.title: McKesson Plaza - 1 Post Street, San Francisco

description._content:
1969, Welton Becket & Associates
A.k.a. 1 Post Plaza, Crocker Center, Aetna Building

Tower on left, partially visible is Pacific Telesis Tower, aka Telesis Tower, Post-Montgomery Center and 120 Kearny Street. 1982, Skidmore, Owings & Merrill.  Despite address, tower does not border Montgomery Street. It stands at the northeast corner of Post and Kearny Streets.
